    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a pristine 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) in collector-grade condition. This wide-body variant features the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering linear power through a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This example has been meticulously maintained, featuring a proactive LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The chassis retains its factory-specified rigidity, supported by the Porsche Stability Management (PSM) system and a viscous-clutch all-wheel-drive assembly. The braking system utilizes four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing zero fade. Finished in Arctic Silver, the paint depth is consistent across all panels with no evidence of oxidation or road rash. A mechanically flawless example for the discerning enthusiast seeking peak 996 performance.",
